'''MATE''' is a fork of GNOME 2 by The MATE team; according to their manifesto they aim to keep a traditional desktop, maintain an open development model, have an open relationship with GNU/Linux distributions and also serve as a good alternative for lower end hardware.

== Installation ==

=== Layman ===

First, you need to obtain layman to be able to get the MATE overlay; follow the [[Layman]] article to install it, then run the following command:

{{RootCmd|layman -a mate}}

=== MATE ===

To install MATE, you can then run the following command:

{{RootCmd|emerge mate-base/mate}}

